race.comment: Competitive affair. MANNERHEIM (10) loves it here at the Doomben circuit only missing a drum once in six spins and will be high on confidence following that last-start victory. Winning jockey Thompson is back on deck and maps perfectly for this from gate five. Rates the testing material. MR BUSTER (11) returned in good order with a close-up second here and will be much better for that hit-out. Has the ability to mix it with them. CAVALRY MAN (3) hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner Positive Peace) and should be ready for the step-up in trip now. Top-three credentials on best form. KALUAKOI (6) gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim and should be in this for a long way. TWIGMAN (1) wasn't too far off them in the Port Macquarie Cup last time out and will find this assignment a touch easier. In the mix.
